The paper deals with time bounds for streaming problems, which are typically studied in the data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL) communities. The use of the cell probe model suggests a focus on computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the specific problems studied (convolution, multiplication, and Hamming distance) are related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
